<item>
            <title>[FLINK-5027] FileSource finishes successfully with a wrong path</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-5027</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When reading from a non existing &lt;tt&gt;File&lt;/tt&gt; or a wrong file path, a Flink streaming program finishes successfully even though it should fail with a appropriate error message. This can be misleading since the user is not notified about the wrong file path. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the default behaviour should be that we fail a file streaming source if the file path is wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
