                            <comment id="15644507" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 7 Nov 2016 15:38:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user kl0u opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2765&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2765&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-5027&quot; title=&quot;FileSource finishes successfully with a wrong path&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-5027&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-5027&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; FileSource finishes successfully with a wrong path&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Adds a test in the `run()` of the `ContinuousFileMonitoringFunction` that checks if the user-specified path is valid. If not, the job will throw an IOException at runtime. We cannot throw the exception at compile time as we may not have access to the cluster.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    R: @tillrohrmann &lt;/p&gt;

